nce >= 0.8\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: L-Alanine\nOVERALL STRATEGY: The network targets L-alanine through a densely connected prebiotic graph centered on four hubs: hydrogen cyanide, formaldehyde, pyruvate, and lactate. Hydrothermal chemistry fixes CO2 into formate, acetate, formaldehyde, and pyruvate on iron-sulfur and iron-oxide minerals. Surface environments convert hydrothermal feedstocks into sugars, nitriles, aminonitriles, and amino acids through cyanosulfidic photochemistry, Strecker-type chemistry, aldol chemistry, and wet-dry concentration on borate, sulfide, TiO2, phosphate, and clay minerals. Biochemical/prebiotic settings then interconvert pyruvate, lactate, acetaldehyde, and alanine by reductive amination, transamination, and peptide assembly. Ten valid pathways to L-alanine are embedded, with multiple convergent routes at pyruvate and acetaldehyde and cross-environment transfer from hydrothermal products to surface synthesis and then to biochemical assembly.\n\nMOLECULES (16 nodes):\n  - mol_001: CO2 (carbon dioxide) [starting]\n  - mol_002: H2 (hydrogen) [starting]\n  - mol_003: NH3 (ammonia) [starting]\n  - mol_004: HCN (hydrogen cyanide) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_005: CH2O2 (formic acid/formate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_006: CH2O (formaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_007: C2H4O2 (glycolaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_008: C3H6O3 (glyceraldehyde) [intermediate]\n  - mol_009: C2H4O2 (acetate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_010: C3H4O3 (pyruvic acid) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_011: C3H4N2 (alanine aminonitrile) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_012: C3H7NO2 (L-alanine) [target]\n  - mol_013: C3H6O3 (lactic acid/lactate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_014: C2H4O (acetaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_015: CH3NO (formamide) [intermediate]\n  - mol_016: C3H5NO (2-aminoacrolein) [intermediate]\n\nREACTIONS (16 nodes):\n  - rxn_001: mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_005 (Greigite-catalyzed reduction of carbon dioxide to formate) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_002: mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_006 (Magnetite/iron reduction of carbon dioxide to formaldehyde via hydrothermal hydrogenation) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_003: mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_009 (Hydrothermal synthesis of acetate from carbon dioxide and hydrogen) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_004: mol_005, mol_009, mol_002 -> mol_010 (Hydrothermal carboxylative synthesis of pyruvate) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_005: mol_005, mol_003 -> mol_004 (Surface UV cyanosulfidic generation of hydrogen cyanide from formate-derived reduced carbon) [Surface]\n  - rxn_006: mol_006 -> mol_007 (Borate-stabilized dimerization of formaldehyde to glycolaldehyde) [Surface]\n  - rxn_007: mol_007, mol_006 -> mol_008 (Aldol extension of glycolaldehyde to glyceraldehyde) [Surface]\n  - rxn_008: mol_014, mol_003, mol_004 -> mol_011 (Strecker-type synthesis of alanine aminonitrile from acetaldehyde) [Surface]\n  - rxn_009: mol_011 -> mol_012 (Hydrolysis of alanine aminonitrile to alanine) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_010: mol_010, mol_003, mol_002 -> mol_012 (Hydrothermal reductive amination of pyruvate to alanine) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_011: mol_010, mol_002 -> mol_013 (Reduction of pyruvate to lactate in prebiotic pools) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_012: mol_013, mol_003 -> mol_012 (Transamination-like conversion of lactate to alanine) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_013: mol_010 -> mol_014, mol_001 (Thermal decarboxylation of pyruvate to acetaldehyde) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_014: mol_004 -> mol_015 (HCN hydration to formamide under UV-active surface conditions) [Surface]\n  - rxn_015: mol_007, mol_004, mol_003 -> mol_016 (Condensation of glycolaldehyde with HCN and ammonia to 2-aminoacrolein) [Surface]\n  - rxn_016: mol_016, mol_002 -> mol_011 (Conversion of 2-aminoacrolein to alanine aminonitrile) [Biochemical]\n\nPATHWAYS (10):\n  - P1: Direct hydrothermal reductive amination route (4 steps)\n  - P2: Hydrothermal pyruvate to lactate to alanine route (5 steps)\n  - P3: Pyruvate decarboxylation followed by Strecker synthesis (6 steps)\n  - P4: Formate to HCN to Strecker route via pyruvate-derived acetaldehyde (7 steps)\n  - P5: Formaldehyde-sugar branch feeding aminonitrile formation (5 steps)\n  - P6: Formaldehyde to glycolaldehyde to glyceraldehyde side branch into alanine network (6 steps)\n  - P7: HCN-formamide auxiliary route merging with Strecker alanine synthesis (8 steps)\n  - P8: Acetate-assisted hydrothermal pyruvate route to alanine (4 steps)\n  - P9: Acetate-assisted hydrothermal pyruvate route via acetaldehyde Strecker branch (6 steps)\n  - P10: Integrated cross-environment hub route (9 steps)\n\nHUB MOLECULES: mol_004, mol_006, mol_010, mol_011, mol_014\nCONVERGENCE POINTS: 5\n\n\nPlease evaluate the network and respond with JSON:\n{\n    \"pathway_evaluations\": [\n        {\n            \"pathway_id\": \"<id>\",\n            \"reaction_scores\": {\"rxn_001\": 0.85, ...},\n            \"chemical_feasibility\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"pathway_coherence\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"environmental_progression\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"target_achievement\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"overall_confidence\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"feedback\": \"<pathway-specific feedback>\",\n            \"approved\": <true if confidence >= 0.8>,\n            \"problematic_reactions\": [\"rxn_ids with issues\"],\n            \"suggestions\": [\"improvements\"]\n        }\n    ],\n    \"best_pathway_id\": \"<id of best pathway>\",\n    \"overall_confidence\": <0.0-1.0>,\n    \"network_feedback\": \"<overall assessment>\",\n    \"approved\": <true if any pathway approved>,\n    \"hub_quality\": <0.0-1.0>,\n    \"convergence_quality\": <0.0-1.0>\n}\n", "raw_response": "{\n  \"pathway_evaluations\": [\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P1\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_001\": 0.86,\n        \"rxn_003\": 0.8,\n        \"rxn_004\": 0.62,\n        \"rxn_010\": 0.72\n      },\n   