icit mineral/photochemical context for carbonyl chemistry."]}, {"pathway_id": "P5", "reaction_scores": {"rxn_005": 0.42, "rxn_006": 0.35, "rxn_007": 0.72, "rxn_014": 0.22, "rxn_004": 0.8, "rxn_011": 0.86, "rxn_013": 0.87, "rxn_008": 0.28}, "chemical_feasibility": 0.49, "pathway_coherence": 0.62, "environmental_progression": 0.82, "target_achievement": 0.88, "overall_confidence": 0.6, "feedback": "This route suffers from compounding weaknesses: problematic formaldehyde-to-glycolaldehyde stoichiometry, a speculative glyceraldehyde-to-pyruvate step, and an underjustified formamide-to-HCN step. Although the later Strecker and hydrolysis stages are good, the upstream chemistry is too uncertain.", "approved": false, "problematic_reactions": ["rxn_005", "rxn_006", "rxn_014", "rxn_008"], "suggestions": ["Rebuild the sugar branch using accepted formose-type stoichiometry.", "Use a more established cyanide source.", "Reduce pathway length by avoiding multiple speculative transformations before the robust Strecker step."]}, {"pathway_id": "P6", "reaction_scores": {"rxn_008": 0.28, "rxn_009": 0.9, "rxn_010": 0.58, "rxn_011": 0.86, "rxn_013": 0.87}, "chemical_feasibility": 0.68, "pathway_coherence": 0.8, "environmental_progression": 0.86, "target_achievement": 0.89, "overall_confidence": 0.74, "feedback": "HCN oligomerization to DAMN is strong, and DAMN/HCN photochemical cycling is directionally plausible. But this pathway depends heavily on rxn_008, which is weakly framed. If HCN availability were better justified, this route would become much stronger.", "approved": false, "problematic_reactions": ["rxn_008", "rxn_010"], "suggestions": ["Introduce HCN as an exogenous atmospheric/surface input or from more established cyanide-producing chemistry.", "Clarify whether DAMN recycling is net productive or only a buffering reservoir."]}, {"pathway_id": "P7", "reaction_scores": {"rxn_001": 0.88, "rxn_003": 0.62, "rxn_004": 0.8, "rxn_011": 0.86, "rxn_013": 0.87, "rxn_008": 0.28}, "chem